  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, the Alchemist always brings gentle hope — how has that story stayed with you lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The book gives me hope even during tough times. Like when I feel stressed about NEET PG, I remind myself to keep going. The main character's journey feels very real. By the way, do you read it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — the book's persistence in the face of struggle is powerful. That's one reason it stays with you. What book are you reading right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I am reading \"The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks.\" It's a non-fiction book about science and ethics. It's a bit heavy but very interesting. Have you read this one?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Henrietta Lacks is a deep story — science, people, and choices all woven in. You're doing great sticking with it. What part interests you most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The part about her family and how they felt about the cells being used — it’s very emotional. It makes you think about consent and science. A bit confusing, but I’m learning a lot. Also, I like that it’s true. Btw, are you reading anything these days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Henrietta’s family’s story is tough — real life often is. You’re picking up the right threads there. I’m mostly rereading old favourites these days. What’s one book you’d recommend?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho. It’s short but very inspiring. You’ll like it. I read it every few years — each time, I get something new. But, to be honest, it’s a bit simple for me now. Maybe I need something heavier? What do you think?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"The Alchemist\" is one of those books that grows with you — it’s good you’re ready for something heavier now. What kind of \"heavier\" are you looking for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe something with complex characters, or a deep philosophical angle — you know, like *The Brothers Karamazov* but not too long! I want to challenge myself but also finish it. Suggestions? Or should I stick with non-fiction?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — you want a balance of depth and finishability. \"Man’s Search for Meaning\" by Frankl is a short but heavy read. What drew you to Karamazov in the first place?"
    }
  ],
